@startuml circular-buffer-state
!theme plain
title Bike Black Box – Circular Buffer State Machine
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam stateBorderColor #2980B9
skinparam stateArrowColor #2C3E50
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9E7
skinparam noteBorderColor #F39C12

' ──────────────────────────────────────────
' STATES
' ──────────────────────────────────────────
[*] --> Idle : System boot\nRecovery complete\nFile lists rebuilt

state Idle {
  Idle : entry / load existing file lists from disk
  Idle : do   / monitor disk usage (passive)
  Idle : exit / --
}

state Writing {
  Writing : entry / register new chunk in file list
  Writing : do   / append (filename, timestamp, size_mb) to list
  Writing : do   / accumulate total_mb
  Writing : exit / check total_mb vs threshold
}

state Threshold_Exceeded {
  Threshold_Exceeded : entry / find oldest file (min timestamp)
  Threshold_Exceeded : do   / rename file → file.deleting  [atomic]
  Threshold_Exceeded : do   / os.remove(file.deleting)
  Threshold_Exceeded : do   / subtract size_mb from total_mb
  Threshold_Exceeded : exit / log deletion to disk_usage.json
}

state Deleting {
  Deleting : entry / execute atomic delete sequence
  Deleting : do   / rename → .deleting
  Deleting : do   / remove .deleting
  Deleting : do   / update stats (deleted++, freed_mb += sz)
  Deleting : exit / persist disk_usage.json to /blackbox/state/
}

state Error {
  Error : entry / log exception to /blackbox/logs/storage.log
  Error : do   / skip current deletion attempt
  Error : exit / schedule retry on next chunk write
}

' ──────────────────────────────────────────
' TRANSITIONS
' ──────────────────────────────────────────
Idle --> Writing            : on_new_chunk(camera, filename, size_mb)\ncalled by camera service

Writing --> Idle            : total_mb ≤ threshold (2500 MB)\n[no deletion needed]

Writing --> Threshold_Exceeded : total_mb > threshold (2500 MB)\n[must free space]

Threshold_Exceeded --> Deleting     : oldest file identified\n[atomic rename succeeds]

Threshold_Exceeded --> Threshold_Exceeded : total_mb still > threshold\nafter one deletion\n[loop until below threshold]

Threshold_Exceeded --> Error        : oldest file not found\nor rename/remove fails

Deleting --> Threshold_Exceeded     : total_mb still > threshold\n[delete another chunk]

Deleting --> Idle                   : total_mb ≤ threshold\n[buffer back in bounds]

Error --> Idle                      : exception logged\ncontinue without deletion

' ──────────────────────────────────────────
' NOTES
' ──────────────────────────────────────────
note right of Idle
  File lists are rebuilt from
  filesystem on each boot
  (no in-memory state is persisted).
end note

note right of Writing
  Both front and rear camera lists
  are maintained separately but
  checked against a single combined
  threshold of 2,500 MB (~1 hour
  of dual 5 Mbps video).
end note

note right of Threshold_Exceeded
  Oldest file is determined by
  comparing the earliest timestamp
  across both front and rear lists.
  Paired front+rear chunks are NOT
  deleted together – each is treated
  independently by timestamp.
end note

note right of Deleting
  Atomic delete on ext4:
  1. rename(file, file.deleting)
     — visible in directory but
       flagged as in-progress
  2. remove(file.deleting)
     — final unlink

  If power is lost between steps 1
  and 2, the .deleting file is an
  orphan cleaned up on next boot.
end note

@enduml
